  "prompt": "What are some good gay romance movies?",
  "response": "There are several excellent gay romance movies that you might enjoy. Here\u2019s a list that includes a mix of classic and contemporary films across different styles and themes:\n\n1. **Call Me by Your Name (2017)** - A coming-of-age romance set in 1980s Italy, this film explores the passionate relationship between a 17-year-old and his father's research assistant.\n\n2. **Moonlight (2016)** - This Academy Award-winning film follows the life of a young Black man from childhood to adulthood, grappling with his identity and sexuality while growing up in a rough neighborhood of Miami.\n\n3. **Brokeback Mountain (2005)** - A landmark film in gay cinema, it tells the story of two cowboys who develop a complex and deep emotional and sexual relationship over several years.\n\n4. **The Handmaiden (2016)** - This South Korean film combines romance, thriller, and a twisty plot, focusing on a con artist and her wealthy heiress target.\n\n5. **Love, Simon (2018)** - A coming-of-age story about a high school student who is navigating his identity while trying to find love and accept himself.\n\n6. **Pride (2014)** - Based on a true story, this film depicts the alliance between LGBTQ activists and striking miners in 1980s Wales.\n\n7. **Carol (2015)** - Set in the 1950s, this beautiful film follows the forbidden love affair between an aspiring photographer and an older woman going through a difficult divorce.\n\n8. **God\u2019s Own Country (2017)** - A raw and intimate film about a young farmer in Yorkshire who finds love during an unexpected connection with a Romanian migrant worker.\n\n9. **Portrait of a Lady on Fire (2019)** - This French film depicts the romance between an artist and her subject in 18th-century France, exploring themes of forbidden love and art.\n\n10. **Weekend (2011)** - A thoughtful and tender film about a one-night stand between two men that develops into a deeper connection over the course of a weekend.\n\nThese films offer a range of experiences and narratives within the LGBTQ+ community, showcasing love, struggle, and personal growth.",
